      • rewriteFix

        public static Fix rewriteFix(HintContext ctx,
                             String displayName,
                             TreePath what,
                             String to)
        Prepare a fix that will replace the given tree node (what) with the given code. Any variables in the to pattern will be replaced with their values from HintContext.getVariables(), HintContext.getMultiVariables() and HintContext.getVariableNames().
        Parameters:
        ctx - basic context for which the fix should be created
        displayName - the display name of the fix
        what - the tree node that should be replaced
        to - the new code that should replaced the what tree node
        Returns:
        an editor fix that performs the required transformation

      • isPrimary

        public static boolean isPrimary(@NonNull
                                Tree tree)
        Checks whether tree can be used in places where a Primary is required (for instance, as the receiver expression of a method invocation).

        This is a friend API intended to be used by the java.hints module. Other modules should not use this API because it might not be stabilized.

        Parameters:
        tree - the tree to check
        Returns:
        true iff tree can be used where a Primary is required.
        Since:
        1.31

      • requiresParenthesis

        public static boolean requiresParenthesis(Tree inner,
                                          Tree original,
                                          Tree outter)
        Checks whether putting inner tree into outter tree, when original is being replaced with inner requires parentheses.
        Parameters:
        inner - the new tree node that will be placed under outter
        original - the tree node that is being replaced with inner
        outter - the future parent node of inner
        Returns:
        true if and only if inner needs to be wrapped using TreeMaker.Parenthesized(com.sun.source.tree.ExpressionTree) to keep the original meaning.
